cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes a new model for knowledge base completion that uses a controller and shared memory to perform multi-step inference implicitly. The paper also uses embedding neural space to learn multi-step relations from training data. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the proposed model uses neural networks to learn embeddings and perform inference. 

The paper may also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as knowledge base completion. 

Additionally, it may belong to cs.DB (Databases) as it deals with knowledge bases and their completion. 

Finally, it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses neural networks to perform multi-step inference.
